+## [2026-07-09T15:50:32Z] tui — focused task info panel
+
+**Action:** Reworked the grid-mode `i` gesture from the legacy bottom-strip idea preview into a full-screen read-only task info panel. The panel follows the TUI MVU boundary documented in [[commands/tui]]: `KeyMap` emits `OpenInfoPanel`, `BubbleModel` performs bounded local filesystem reads from `idea.md`, stage markdown, and latest task logs, `Update` only flips pure state via `InfoPanelOpened`, and `Views::InfoPanel` renders the captured payload. It does not dispatch workflow commands, mutate markers, open an editor/pager, call git, or call the network. The footer legend now includes `[i] info`; the `?` help overlay was intentionally left unchanged for this iteration.
+
+**Refreshed pages:**
+- [[commands/tui]] — documented the info-panel mode, `i` keybinding, footer legend, close keys, local read-only payload, and temporary help-copy drift.
+
+## [2026-07-09T16:09:36Z] tui — info panel review fixes
+
+**Action:** Fixed review-pass issues in the focused task info panel. `Model::InfoPanelState` now carries the opened row's `project_name`, and `Update` uses folder plus `project_name`/slug/stage identity to restore the cursor to the same visible card when the panel closes after a background `SnapshotArrived` reorder. `BubbleModel` now parses complete `idea.md` frontmatter with YAML when available, but falls back to a bounded literal-block scanner for oversized `original_text` blocks whose closing fence is beyond the display cap, so the panel opens with a truncation indicator instead of flashing in grid mode. Added regression coverage for same-card close after reorder, oversized frontmatter truncation, and unreadable stage-artifact handling.
+
+**Refreshed pages:**
+- [[commands/tui]] — documented same-card close restoration and bounded large-frontmatter behavior for the info panel.
+
+## [2026-07-09T16:28:00Z] tui — keep info-panel stage context visible
+
+**Action:** Adjusted the focused task info panel render priority so stage-specific context (`brainstorm.md`, `plan.md`, or the latest execute-log tail) appears before the original idea body. This keeps the stage artifact visible when a long original idea exhausts the panel row budget, while preserving the existing bounded-read behavior and read-only MVU flow.
+
+**Refreshed pages:**
+- [[commands/tui]] — documented the stage-context-first render order for the info panel.
